<div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />Whenever the half-prepared 2C02 gets delayered, we'll get Visual2C02 and to find out all sorts of  magic.<br /><br />Personally, I'm really curious what the data sent over the EXT bus is.<br /></div><br />Somebody on IRC said that the data is the palette index (index in to the palette sets) currently being rendered by the PPU. But since the bus is only 4 bits wide, it's not possible to know if the given index refers to the background or sprite palette.<br /><br />As an input, the 4 bit value refers to the full 16 color background palette set. In NES the bits are grounded, so the background always uses color #0.<br /><br />I have not verified this, nor was I given a source for the information so take it with a grain of salt.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Fri May 11, 2012 2:59 am</p><hr />
