Especially when this sort of sparse sample playback (or "piecewise linear mode" as I'll call it) can be done on an unmodified NES. Make one-byte samples of value $AA (flat), $00 (decrease), and $FF (increase). Then play individual bytes after each DMC IRQ, writing the starting value of a segment to $4011 and the address of the direction to $4012.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Thu May 10, 2012 5:18 am</p><hr />
